'''Dominique Parodi''' (May 2, 1870 – November 12, 1955) was a French philosopher and educational administrator.
Dominique Parodi was born in [[Genoa]]. A member of the group around [[Émile Durkheim]], he was a contributor to their journal, ''[[L'Année Sociologique]]''.<ref name="Pickering1979">{{cite book|editor=W. S. F. Pickering|title=Durkheim: essays on morals and education|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pEnwAAAAIAAJ|accessdate=26 December 2012|year=1979|publisher=Routledge & Kegan Paul|isbn=978-0-7100-0321-8|page=76}}</ref> Between 1919 and 1934 he was General Inspector of Public Instruction. He succeeded [[Xavier Léon]] as editor of the ''[[Revue de métaphysique et de morale]]'', editing it from 1935 to 1955.<ref name="Schrift2009">{{cite book|author=Alan D. Schrift|title=Twentieth-Century French Philosophy: Key Themes and Thinkers|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=arsVNvotJa4C&pg=PA17|accessdate=26 December 2012|date=4 February 2009|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-4051-4394-3|pages=17–}}</ref>
